# Project Overview

Locate Travel provides two ways for users to generate travel routes.

1. Users can manually enter a destination name and receive the shortest route from their current location.
2. Users can upload an image of a place they want to visit.

When an image is uploaded, the system first checks whether the image contains GPS metadata. If location metadata exists, the system extracts the coordinates to identify the location.

If the metadata is missing or unreliable, the system analyzes the image using computer vision techniques. If recognizable landmarks are detected, the system estimates the location based on those features.

If the image does not contain identifiable landmarks, the system allows the user to provide contextual hints such as the country or city where the photo was taken. These hints help narrow down candidate locations using a place search API. The system then compares the uploaded image with candidate images to estimate the most likely location.

After the destination is identified, the system generates the shortest travel route from the user's current location to the destination and displays it on the web interface.

---

