│ └ Image Embedding (CLIP)
│
├── Places API
│ └ Candidate Location Search
│
└── Directions API
└ Shortest Route Generation
│
▼
Frontend Map Visualization


# Workflow

1. User uploads an image or enters a destination.
2. The backend checks whether the image contains GPS metadata.
3. If GPS metadata exists, the system uses it to determine the location.
4. If GPS metadata is not available, the system analyzes the image using computer vision.
5. If landmarks are detected, the system estimates the location.
6. If the location cannot be inferred, the user may provide contextual hints such as country or city.
7. The system searches candidate locations using a place search API.
8. Image similarity techniques are used to estimate the most likely location.
9. Once the location is identified, the system generates the shortest route to the destination.
10. The route is displayed on the map in the web interface.

